lities on both parameters\nthat are studied numerically. In all cases $\\lambda$ is restricted by $\\mu$\naround $1/3$ and we obtain $\\lambda\\to1/3$ if $\\mu\\to0$. Finally we consider\nthe $f(R)$ limit $\\mu,\\lambda\\to1$ and we obtain consistent results.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Feb 2023 18:16:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-20"}
